Besides crystalline and amorphous solids, there are some solids which apparently appear amorphous but have microcrystalline structures.", "fibs": ["Table"]}
{"text": "Metals often occur in polycrystalline condition.", "fibs": ["condition"]}
{"text": "Individual crystals are randomly oriented so a metallic sample may appear to be isotropic even though a single crystal is anisotropic.", "fibs": ["sample"]}
{"text": "Glass, rubber and plastics find many applications in our daily lives.", "fibs": ["rubber"]}
{"text": "Amorphous silicon is one of the best photovoltaic material available for conversion of sunlight into electricity.", "fibs": ["silicon"]}
